nodes.title: Note // About
widgets_values:
Module #4 // Animation Generator v1.5 // About . . .
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
              >>>For Creating Animations<<<
---------------------------------------------------------------
---------------------------------------------------------------
This modules aim is to provide a multitude of ways to create animations, from text, video, and images. New workflows are marked with an *, before their name in the list.
-------------------------------------------------------------
Sound executes upon completion - be aware of the volume - it should be around 0.1 - which is low. (red node/playsound)
-------------------------------------------------------------
SVD has a non-commercial liscense. Be sure to check it out.
-------------------------------------------------------------
Insight-face also has a non-commercial liscense. Recommeded 
to use Mediapipe for Live Portrait for commercial purposes.
-------------------------------------------------------------
Important: Mute or bypass nodes further down the sequential line of a group to shorten generation times or to lessen v-ram usage by the generation.
-------------------------------------------------------------
Text to Video: Use text to create a animation. Uses some experimental settings, which you can bypass if you don't like the results.
-------------------------------------------------------------
Video to Video: Load a video to modify. Also Uses some experimental settings, which you can bypass if you don't like the results.
-------------------------------------------------------------
Attention Masking & Image Composite to Video: Use attention masking to create an animation from 3 separate images. You will need a mask with 3 color values, red, green, and blue. I use 2 face detailers and 2 hand detailers here, though they may not be necessary for some. Example masks here:
https://imgur.com/a/lfR8d2G
-------------------------------------------------------------
Inpaint Image to Video: 
Inpaint/mask parts of an image to animate and prompt what you would like to see. Recommended to use an inpaint model.
-------------------------------------------------------------
Video Upscale: 
A simple way to upscale and clean up a video. 
-------------------------------------------------------------
Image to Video (SVD): Lots of experimenting usually needed with SVD to get a good result. A lot of the parameters change the video output, so you'll need to test things out to get what you want. There is no prompting for SVD at the moment. 
-------------------------------------------------------------
Simple Frame Interpolation: Use a start and end image to create frames between two images. It's a way for the AI to guess the sequence of events between the two images you provide.
-------------------------------------------------------------
MotionDiff & SMPL: An interesting way to create 3D character animations from text prompts to use in your generations or on your actual 3D characters. SMPL's are created on the top half of the group and then exported to your output folder in comfyui. You will need to transfer the exports to your input folder in order to load them for the bottom portion of video generation (or you could change the smpl export path).
https://github.com/Fannovel16/ComfyUI-MotionDiff
-------------------------------------------------------------
Video Remove Background #1: A simple way to remove the background of your videos. Video Combine has some issue rendering the transparent images to .mp4, so for now the images are saved in batches and can be re-assmebled into a video.
https://github.com/chflame163/ComfyUI_LayerStyle
-------------------------------------------------------------
*Video Remove Background #2: An alternative method to removing the background in a video. Doesn't save images in batches, it does direct to video instead.
https://github.com/yolain/ComfyUI-Easy-Use
-------------------------------------------------------------
*ControlNeXt SVD: Functions similar to mimic-motion in that it adds the motion of a driving video to a static image.
https://github.com/kijai/ComfyUI-ControlNeXt-SVD
-------------------------------------------------------------
*MimicMotion: Takes the motion of a video and applies it to an image. Essentially you can make still images dance or wave or whatever with a driving video.
https://github.com/kijai/ComfyUI-MimicMotionWrapper
-------------------------------------------------------------
*Image Live Portrait: Use a driving video to control the expression of an animal or person in a image. Mediapipe is reccommended for commercial. Insightface is better overall.
https://github.com/kijai/ComfyUI-LivePortraitKJ
-------------------------------------------------------------
*Video Live Portrait: Also uses a driving video to control the expression of an animal or person, only this does it in a video. Mediapipe is reccommended for commercial - insightface is better overall.
https://github.com/kijai/ComfyUI-LivePortraitKJ
-------------------------------------------------------------
*Advanced Live Portrait #1: Animate expressions without driving videos, simply using node configurations.
https://github.com/PowerHouseMan/ComfyUI-AdvancedLivePortrait 
-------------------------------------------------------------
*Advanced Live Portrait #2: Simple expression adjustment for images.
https://github.com/PowerHouseMan/ComfyUI-AdvancedLivePortrait
-------------------------------------------------------------
*Advanced Live Portrait #3: Simple expression adjustment for videos.
https://github.com/PowerHouseMan/ComfyUI-AdvancedLivePortrait
-------------------------------------------------------------
*IC-Light Animated #1: This is for adding animated light to images, adjust the spline for different results. Press the ? on the upper right corner of the node for more information.
https://github.com/kijai/ComfyUI-IC-Light
-------------------------------------------------------------
*IC-Light Animated #2: This is for adding animated light to background of images, adjust the splines for different results. Press the ? on the upper right corner of the node for more information.
https://github.com/kijai/ComfyUI-IC-Light
-------------------------------------------------------------
*Florence2 & SAM2: Utilizes the Florence2 model for object tracking and the SAM2 model for segmentation of the tracked object.
https://github.com/kijai/ComfyUI-segment-anything-2 
-------------------------------------------------------------
*SAM2 Point Segmentation: Uses the Point Editor to manually segment object by placing the green points on what you want to segment. Very unstable node sizing when using at the time of writing this. May improve in future updates. Be sure to clear the image or delete and replace the node before sharing as apparently the image gets saved in the node, including workflows, so caution. Press the ? for more info on the node.
https://github.com/kijai/ComfyUI-segment-anything-2
-------------------------------------------------------------
Node Color Information Below:

nodes.title: Note // Extra Information
widgets_values:
Module #3 // Compositing & Editing v1.5 // Extra Info . . .
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Website: https://aemotionstudio.org/
Youtube: https://www.youtube.com/@aemotionstudio
Civitai: https://civitai.com/user/AEmotionStudio
Github: https://github.com/AEmotionStudio
-------------------------------------------------------------
All modules here are uniform and have a left-to-right, top-to-bottom flow (sequential flow). Meaning they read just like a book. No nodes are hidden and all similar or branching nodes are grouped together accordingly. This aims to solve the organizational problem that most other workflows have and to simplify the creation process. All nodes are also color coded.
-------------------------------------------------------------
Main model used - Dreamshaper 8: 
https://civitai.com/models/4384?modelVersionId=128713
-------------------------------------------------------------
All IPAdapter models can be found in the Comfy UI Manager Install Models tab. Type "faceid" in the search for quick picks. Update all if you run into further issues.
-------------------------------------------------------------
Experiment with different batch sizes for the "emptyimage // experimental settings" node for different results. The color value also has an added effect. I've also added more options for color modifications. This is experimental and you can bypass them if you don't like the results. 
-------------------------------------------------------------
For SDXL & LCM simply change models and parameters to match.
-------------------------------------------------------------
All groups are pinned - to unpin them - right click and select unpin while hovering over the group.
-------------------------------------------------------------
Trouble Shooting InsightFace:

First, make sure your ComfyUI and nodes are updated. Then try switching the LivePortrait Load InsightFaceCropper from CPU to CUDA and vice versa if they are switched.

If you experience this error: "No Module InsightFace"
Remove Reactor Nodes if you have them installed, then manually install insightface. ((This may have been resolved in an update but useful to know how the problem was orignally solved)) 
Follow the troubleshoot guide here:
https://github.com/Gourieff/comfyui-reactor-node#insightfacebuild
-------------------------------------------------------------
Trouble Shooting DW Pose Estimator:
- Open CMD in ComfyUI_windows_portable folder
- Use: python_embeded\python.exe -m pip install -U onnx onnxruntime onnxruntime-gpu
For more information:
https://github.com/Fannovel16/comfyui_controlnet_aux/issues/102#issuecomment-1848365343
-------------------------------------------------------------

a. You are solely responsible for any legal liability resulting from your use of these workflows.
b. The creator(s) of these workflows disclaim any responsibility for misuse or unethical use of the workflows or their outputs.
c. The creator(s) of these workflows are not liable for any damages claimed to result from the use of these Workflows, including but not limited to direct, indirect, incidental, or consequential damages.
---------------------------------------------------------------
Thanks to all the creators of the wonderful nodes and models used herein!
-------------------------------------------------------------
Created By: Æmotion Studio
